  "texts": [
    "• We leveraged the comprehensive O'Neil drug interaction dataset that ensuring robustness across cancer types and relying on curated data strengthens our findings.",
    "• The proposed model successfully identified combination pairs that shows the highest likelihood of synergy against specific cancers.",
    "Notably, coupling kinase inhibitors with mTOR, DNA damage or HDAC inhibitors showed promise, highlighting strategies for effective multi-drug regimens.",
    "• We examined drug features and mechanisms to understand why certain pairs synergize which focusing on consistently effective drugs like gemcitabine, MK-8776, and AZD1775 against various cancers added context.",
    "Finally, systematically uncovering advantageous multi-drug options has potential to inform clinical decision making."
